Korean books presented to Mexican political party 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Korean books were presented to the Mexican Worker's Party, among them celebrated works of the great leaders President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A ceremony of presenting the books took place in Mexico on October 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Alberto Anaya Gutierrez, coordinator (leader) of the party national executive committee, said those famous works of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il are precious documents giving a scientific exposition of problems arising in the building of a new society. The Mexican Worker's Party will value the books as treasure and distribute them to local party organizations so that they can take them as a guideline in their activities, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We are convinced that Korea's reunification will be surely realized according to the policy of Kim Jong Il, and extend our firm solidarity to it, he said.

Kim Jong Il's work released in Laos 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- The Lao State Publishing House brought out in booklet General Secretary Kim Jong Il's celebrated work "On Preserving the Juche Character and National Character of the Revolution and Construction" on October 2 to commemorate the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Comprehensively expounded in the work published on June 19, Juche 86 (1997) are the essence and necessity of the work of preserving the Juche character and national character of the revolution and construction, and the key and vital significance of firmly maintaining those characters. It also advances tasks and ways of preserving and applying the characters in the revolution and construction.

Greetings to Ugandan President 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to President Yoweri Kaguta Museveni on October 5 on the occasion of the 38th anniversary of the Independence of Uganda. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim in the message extended warm congratulations to Museveni and the Ugandan government and people on the anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Hoping that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries will continue to develop on good terms, he wholeheartedly wished the President and the government of Uganda greater success in the work to achieve peace and stability of the country.

Punishment to gangsters called for 

  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- More than 100 gangsters of the South Korean "Konkuk Society" and other anti-communist organizations held a "meeting" in Seoul on October 5 at which they staged such disturbing rowdyism as daring provoke the headquarters of our revolution and wantonly challenging the June 15 north-south joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Die-hard anti-communist, anti-reunification elements swaggered about in the heart of Seoul in broad daylight to sling mud at the system in the north, quite unhindered by the South Korean authorities, at a time when the historic north-south joint declaration is being implemented in real earnest and the world is closely following the improvement of the north-south relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This cannot be construed otherwise than a premeditated and deliberate criminal move to bring the north-south relations back to those before the publication of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This rowdyism is by no means an accidental case perpetrated by a few wicked anti-communist elements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This clearly proves to what extent the resistance of the South Korean ultra-right conservative forces against the historic change in the north and south has gone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Thanks to the implementation of the north-south joint declaration the north-south  relations are developing into those of reconciliation and cooperation and the South Korean people came to gradually have a new understanding and view on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The anti-communist right-wing forces, who have survived by fanning up confrontation and division depending on foreign forces are now thrown into a hopeless quandary by this irresistible trend of the history and making desperate efforts to restore their past position and prolong their remaining days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They have been bent on all sorts of wrongs, availing themselves of every opportunity to launch a malignant diatribe intended to incite confrontation and distrust in a bid to bar the mindset in South Korea from turning in favour of alliance and reconciliation with the north and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This notwithstanding, we have proved our true intention and purpose in practice, exercising patience toward their smear campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The grave provocation committed again by anti-communist gangsters through blatant rowdyism, quite unhindered, with the tacit connivance of the authorities, compels the north to strongly doubt the future of the June 15 north-south joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The historical lesson of the north-south relations goes to clearly prove that without liquidating anti-communist, anti-reunification confrontation elements it is impossible to implement any agreement between the north and the south or achieve the country's reunification, the cherished desire of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Those who dare defame the headquarters of our revolution and work hard to stem the trend of national reunification should face severe judgement by history and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If the South Korean authorities has a true will to implement the June 15 north-south joint declaration, they should mercilessly punish the anti-communist gangsters, the anti-reunification criminals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We will closely watch the South Korean authorities' future attitude.

Congratulatory letter to Kim Jong Il from military attaches corps 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory letter from the military attaches corps in Korea on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Vietnamese military attache Vu Dinh Thang, who is doyen of the corps, handed the letter over to an official concerned on sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il also received congratulatory letters and gifts from the military attaches of Vietnam, Iran, Russia, Peru and Egypt, which were conveyed to an official concerned.

Whole country in festive mood 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Tomorrow will mark the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The whole country is wrapped in an atmosphere of festivity and loyalty on the eve of the grand festival of victors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The streets of the capital city of Pyongyang, provinces, cities and counties throughout the country are decorated with slogans reading "the Worker's Party of Korea organizes and guides all victories of our people," "Long live the glorious Worker's Party of Korea founded by the great leader comrade Kim Il Sung and led by the great leader comrade Kim Jong Il " "Long live the benevolent politics, all-embracing politics of our party " "Honor of the DPRK" and "Celebration, welcome," posters, large picture boards and special decorative boards. Decorations, flags and flowers seen in all streets bring joy to the people busy going with flowers and decorations in their hands to greet the great holiday of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The national symposium and oratorical meetings held in commemoration of the 55th anniversary of the WPK lavish praises of the most dignified and veteran ever-victorious WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   An endless stream of working people, servicepersons and school youth and children visit the national book  exhibition, the national fine art exhibition, the national photo exhibition held in different places and the Pyongyang flower show. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Cinema houses where a 10-day film show started are screening documentary films "Leader Is the Great Father of Our People," "Always Believing in People" and "Revolutionary Obligation" and feature films "the County Party Chief Secretary," "the Story of a Party Worker" and "the Taehongdan County Party Chief Secretary" and other films of various themes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The working people across the country have prepared precious gifts to the grand festival of October under the slogan "Let us all become heroes of last charge to glorify the 55th anniversary of the party."   The second stage construction of the Anbyon Youth Power Station, Songwon and Thaechon dam expansion projects, the construction of Thaechon Power Station  no. 5, the thermo-power station of the Ponghwa Chemical Works, the Huichon Chonsang Power Station and the construction of basic foodstuff factories in different provinces have been completed one after another to please the people all out to build a powerful nation.

Juche idea study organizations inaugurated in Tajikistan 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- The Tajik Association for the Study of the Juche Idea Named After General Kim Jong Il was renamed national committee on the occasion of the third anniversary of the great leader Kim Jong Il's election as General Secretary of the Worker's Party of Korea and the 55th anniversary of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The renaming is intended to expand Juche idea study organizations in this country and put the work of studying and disseminating the Juche idea on an organizational basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A meeting was held in Dushanbe on September 30 to rename the association, at which the chief of the youth commission of the Tajik government was selected chairman of the Tajik National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea Named After General Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the meeting, the Kurgan-Tyube city, Khatullon region of Tajikistan, Group for the Study of the Juche Idea Named After General Kim Jong Il was formed and the Tajik Group for the Study of the Juche Idea Named After General Kim Jong Il was renamed the Dushanbe city, Tajikistan, Group for the Study of the Juche Idea Named After General Kim Jong Il.

"Guide to the Juche Idea" published by IIJI 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Book "Guide to the Juche Idea" was published in Japanese by the International Institute of the Juche Idea on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The book, which was written by honorary director general of the IIJI Shuhachi Inoue, consists of a preface, an introduction, 7 chapters with subtitles, including "Fundamental question of philosophy raised by the Juche philosophy and philosophical principles  as an answer to it" and a conclusion "the Juche idea is an immortal guiding idea that leads the independence cause of the DPRK and the whole world to victory."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The writer in the preface says that General Secretary Kim Jong Il has issued many treatises and developed and enriched the Juche philosophy in depth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As he grasps the Juche philosophy deeper and deeper, he feels it is a great philosophy, he says, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Although the power of the pen is not enough to contain the greatness of Kim Jong Il, I hope the book will contribute even a little to the worldwide dissemination of the great Juche idea.

Floral baskets, congratulatory letters and gifts to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received floral baskets, congratulatory letters and gifts from diplomatic envoys of different countries here on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They were conveyed to Kim Yang Gon, department director of the Central Committee of the WPK, and officials concerned by diplomatic envoys of Palestine, Vietnam, Nigeria, Cambodia, Laos, Indonesia, Iran, Libya, Russia, Yugoslavia, India, Egypt, Sweden, Pakistan, Poland, Syria and Yemen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il also received floral baskets and congratulatory letters from the Ethiopian embassy, the resident coordinator of the United Nations and resident representative of the UNDP and the representative of the United Nations Children's Fund to the DPRK.

Unconverted long-term prisoners' view on life praised in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Members of the Thongil Aeguk Society Active in Seoul held a meeting on the subject "Let's live with noble conscience and steadfast faith" on September 17 to praise the view of unconverted long-term prisoners strong in faith on life and express the determination to follow their example, the Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation quoted the Seoul city committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea as saying. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A report and speeches were made at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speaking there, members of the society unanimously described the unconverted long-term prisoners as true teachers of all the pro-reunification activists. And they renewed their resolution to fully discharge their duty as vanguard of the revolutionary movement who display noble conscience and sense of obligation to leader Kim Jong Il, the sun of the nation, and confidence in the sure victory of the cause of reunification any time and any place.

"Korea, Fortress of Socialism" released in Ecuador 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Book "Korea, Fortress of Socialism" was released in Cuenca of Ecuador to commemorate the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The book carries on its front page a picture of the great leaders President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il discussing the work together. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Contained in it are photographs showing the single-heartedly united Korean people and the achievements made by them in socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The book consists of the preface and the three chapters--chapter 1. On Korea, chapter 2. Source of Korea's single-hearted unity and chapter 3. Korean socialism based on trust and unity.

Birthday of WPK to be celebrated in Jordan 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- A Jordanian preparatory committee was formed in Amman on October 2 to celebrate the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The committee consists of political parties and organizations among them the National Action Front Party of Jordan, the Arab Committee for Solidarity with the Korean People and Support to Korea's Reunification, the Arab Center for the Study of the Independence Idea in Jordan and the Arab Christians Committee for Peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It decided to hold multifarious events on the occasion of the WPK's birthday.

Many construction projects completed 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Various construction projects are being completed one after another on the threshold of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The electrification of the narrow-gauge railways between Kanggye and Rangrim was completed on October 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This will help ease the strain in transport in this region and improve traffic for the people there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The thermal power plant of the Ponghwa Chemical Works, the Sinphung Youth Reservoir and a large-scale long-distance belt conveyer inside the pit of the Ryongdung coal mine were also brought to completion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The power plant will generate electricity by making a more effective use of steam available in the course of oil refining. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The operation of a 4,400 meter-long belt conveyer line will help boost the coal production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Among those projects completed are a catfish factory, the Kyenam state farm which will contribute to the improvement of the people's dietary life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The catfish factory covering an area of more than 7,600 square meters looks like a scientific research center. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The factory is capable of producing hundreds of tons of fish a year as it is equipped with all facilities for fish farming including a modern feed processing room, a spawn hatching ground, a breeding pond and an animal matter containing food ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Kyenam state farm with nearly 300 buildings covering an area of over 29,000 square meters is an integrated stock breeding center capable of producing hundreds of tons of a variety of meat a year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This farm is divided into four districts. Two of them have scores of buildings for cows, pigs, goats, rabbits, ducks, geese and pheasants. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It has a good grazing land, a feed processing base, a cheese producing base, a vegetable greenhouse, mushroom cultivation ground. There appeared 90 modern dwelling houses, various service and catering facilities and minor power stations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Besides, Samsong Temple on Mt. Kuwol, a famous mountain of Korea, ancient relics associated with Tangun, ancestral father of the nation, was reconstructed and the construction of the Suan diatomite mine was completed.

"Red Mountain Range" published 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- The Literature and Art Press Group published the novel "Red Mountain Range," a serial of the cycle of novels "Immortal History," created by the April 15 Writing Group on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. It was written by Ri Jong Ryol with the period from the fall of 1939 to the first half of the 1940s for a setting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The novel impressively depicts the tradition of revolutionary faith and will of the Korean revolutionaries established in the bloody anti-Japanese battles thanks to the revolutionary activities conducted by the President Kim Il Sung during that period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The story is set against the backdrop of the situation at a time when wrong views were expressed by flunkeyists and some others on suspending the armed struggle and going underground to preserve revolutionary forces, yielding to the Japanese imperialists' brutal torture and appeasement and deceptive campaign against the revolutionaries and patriots who were arrested on charges of involvement in the "Hyesan incident" sparked by them to destroy all the organizations of the association for the restoration of the fatherland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It gives an impressive depiction of the historical fact that under the situation the President advanced an operational plan to stage a large-unit circling operation and victoriously commanded the arduous Dunhua expedition, the Hongqihe Battle and so on, frustrating the enemy's "punitive campaign" with his outstanding and preeminent tactics and arousing again the once weakened national revolutionary forces to an anti-Japanese war.    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It tells how the President led the guerrillas to struggle with strong revolutionary faith and will overcoming whatever hardship and ordeal and what profound trust and fatherly love he showed for all of them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Through this the novel deals with the truth that when one remains true to his revolutionary faith and conscience, he is immortal and if he gives them up, he will only meet disgrace and a miserable end.

Paean to great party 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today carries an article headlined "Paean to the great party" on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The author of the article says that the unconverted long-term prisoners are very much grateful to the maternal party for saving their destiny and placing them on the height of glory and happiness, and that the party is a huge tree of ideology and faith and they are its small leaves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The article continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As the unconverted long-term prisoners were party members, they could defend their ideology and faith. And as the Worker's Party of Korea has defended socialist ideology, faith and banner, they could lead a life of faith with the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They are veteran party members who have shared the same destiny with the party from the first days of its foundation. Their hearts, soul and lives were given by the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   What they were afraid of was not physical death but the possibility to stain their noble political life given by the party. They lived every moment not to keep their moribund physical life but to glorify the honor of being party members true to the pledge they made when they joined the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They are the unconverted long-term prisoners, the WPK members, who are noblest and purest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As they were party members and given hearts and soul by the party, they could become mental victors over physical death, and men strong in their idea and faith.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Congolese socialist party 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a gift from the Congolese Socialist Party on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The gift was handed to the head of the DPRK delegation staying in Congo on September 28.

Rodong Sinmun on proposal for founding DFRK 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates an article to the 20th anniversary of advancement of the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo (DFRK) by the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The keynote of the proposal expounded by Kim Il Sung in  his report to the sixth congress of the Worker's Party of Korea held on October 10, Juche 69 (1980) is to reunify the country by founding a federal republic through the establishment of a unified national government on condition that the north and the south recognize and tolerate each other's ideas and systems, a government in which the two sides are represented on an equal footing and under which they exercise regional autonomy with equal rights and duties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The proposal is a most fair and aboveboard, reasonable and realistic reunification proposal as it calls for reunifying the country by federal formula based on one nation, one state, two systems and two governments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The proposal most correctly reflects the nature of the reunification issue and the specific reality of Korea among other things. This is based on the original idea and feasibility that different ideas and systems may exist in one country. The proposal reflects the interests of the north and south most equitably. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The proposal defines it as the principle of organizing and constituting a federal state to establish a unified national government in which the north and the south are represented on an equal footing and as the function of the federal state to respect and defend the interests of the whole nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The proposal also calls for applying the principle of impartiality to the operation of the federal state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It also conforms with the interests of neighboring countries as well as all other countries of the world and with the desire of the world peace-loving peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The proposal is based on one nation, one state, two systems and two governments so that it may provide legal and institutional guarantee for the existence of the two systems. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The regional governments in the north and the south shall pursue their own policies under the guidance of the federal government so that neighboring countries may maintain the present relations with the north and the south in many aspects as they are. This is in full accordance with the interests of those countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The peace-loving federal state shall preserve the peace-loving traditions of the Korean nation, give no threat of aggression to any country and not be used by any country for aggression. It shall not build up any armed force aimed at aggression and mass destruction but take it as an immutable guideline of its activity to make the Korean peninsula a peace zone and denuclearized zone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The proposal is a patriotic charter of reunification and a bright blueprint which will bring a reunified country to the Korean nation and guarantee its rosy future. In order to materialize the proposal it is imperative to maintain the principle of national sovereignty, achieve the great unity of the whole nation, remove the threat of war from the Korean peninsula and ensure a durable peace.

Evening galas of youth and students 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Youth and students held evening galas in Pyongyang, counties, cities and provinces on October 8 to mark the 3rd anniversary of the election of the great leader Kim Jong Il as General Secretary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Evening galas of youth and students in Pyongyang took place in different places including plazas of the monument to the Worker's Party of Korea founding, the tower of the Juche idea, the Pyongyang grand theater and the Pyongyang indoor stadium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They danced graceful dances, extending best wishes to the respected leader Kim Jong Il who is leading the WPK to one victory after another. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Songs "Pride of Our Party" and "How Grateful Our Party Is" and other songs that reverberated through the plazas represented the firm determination of the youth and students to become human bombs and suicide bombers devotedly defending the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Evening galas also took place in Chongjin, Hamhung, Kaesong, Nampho and other local cities that day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, art performances of schoolchildren were staged at the Mangyongdae and Pyongyang schoolchildren's palaces to mark the 3rd anniversary of Kim Jong Il's election as General Secretary of the WPK and the 55th anniversary of the WPK.

Representatives of political parties, organizations and individuals from south side here 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Representatives of political parties and organizations and individual personages from the south side arrived here today to participate in the celebrations of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They were met at the airport by Kim Ryong Song, vice-chairman of the National Reconciliation Council, and leading officials of public and religious organizations.

Letters of loyalty to Kim Jong Il conveyed 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of conveying letters of loyalty to the great leader Kim Jong Il in celebration of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea took place at Kim Il Sung Stadium today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The letters carry best wishes and pledge of loyalty of all the people and servicemen to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Letters presented by the officers and men of the people's army, the school youth and children, the people from all provinces and cities, the people's security men and women, the officials of the national institutions, the officials in the field of railways and Koreans in Japan were conveyed to Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly.
